      <pbcore:pbcoreDescriptionDocument>
         <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
         <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Interview with Mark Burnette, 2020-06-11</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
         <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>I can remember going to the environmental center, and I went to the classroom where the little girl that passed away, and I wanted to make sure they were good and they were. The teacher had her seat still available. They were all having honest conversation about the loss, and just how to support one another. That--that was the education part that was occurring still, more so than traditional means.</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:01:03"
                            endTime="00:01:41">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q1</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Would you state your name and tell us a little about your background?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 1</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:01:41"
                            endTime="00:02:45">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q2</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Tell us a little about what you do as a school psychologist for the Sevier County School System?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 2</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:02:45"
                            endTime="00:04:35">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q3</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Can you share with us your experiences in the days and weeks leading up to the wildfire?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 3</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:04:35"
                            endTime="00:06:28">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q4</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Can you talk about what the Fall 2016 semester was like and what concerns you had?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 4</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:06:28"
                            endTime="00:08:46">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q5</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>What part of the county were you in the day of the fire? Can you tell us about what transpired that evening for you?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 5</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:08:46"
                            endTime="00:12:42">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q6</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Can you tell us about your experiences in the days after the wildfire and reconnecting with your colleagues to develop a plan?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 6</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:12:42"
                            endTime="00:14:15">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q7</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Were you responsible for providing guidance to the teachers about how to interact with students?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 7</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:14:15"
                            endTime="00:19:13">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q8</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Can you talk about how your role evolved during the weeks and months after the fire? Did you have the chance to talk to the students?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 8</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:19:13"
                            endTime="00:20:24">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q9</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>From your perspective as a psychologist, how do you find storytelling as a therapeutic process? How else did you see the traumatic experiences being processed by individuals?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 9</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:20:24"
                            endTime="00:23:02">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q10</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>What were some of the stages of trauma that you witnessed?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 10</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:23:02"
                            endTime="00:23:52">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q11</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Concerning the disappearance of students, did you notice a large number of Hispanic students that didn't return after the wildfire?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 11</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:23:52"
                            endTime="00:25:19">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q12</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Being four years out, are people still dealing with this trauma or have they started to move on?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 12</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:25:19"
                            endTime="00:26:25">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q13</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>What would you say the impact on the teachers and students has been as a psychologist?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 13</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:26:25"
                            endTime="00:28:24">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q14</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>You mentioned going through training to deal with this, what impact has the fire left on you?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 14</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:28:24"
                            endTime="00:30:03">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q15</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>How would you say that the fire shaped community relations?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 15</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:30:03"
                            endTime="00:31:02">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q16</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Do you feel like people are better prepared for future disasters?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 16</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:31:02"
                            endTime="00:32:45">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q17</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Right now we're in an ongoing economic and health disaster (COVID-19), can you talk about how it has affected your life?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 17</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:32:45"
                            endTime="00:33:55">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q18</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Was there anything else that was surprising or good that came out of these wildfires?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 18</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:33:55"
                            endTime="00:35:58">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q19</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>Is there anything that we haven't talked about that you would like to speak on?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 19</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
         <pbcore:pbcorePart partType="Interview Questions"
                            startTime="00:35:58"
                            endTime="00:41:58">
            <pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier source="local">20200611_Burnette_Mark_Q20</pbcore:pbcoreIdentifier>
            <pbcore:pbcoreTitle>As a psychologist, in your experience is sharing one's story of a traumatic experience a way to heal?</pbcore:pbcoreTitle>
            <pbcore:pbcoreDescription>Question 20</pbcore:pbcoreDescription>
         </pbcore:pbcorePart>
